A survey conducted by the Manufacturers Association of Nigeria (MAN) among manufacturers’ Chief Executive Officers operating in the country yesterday showed that Nigeria’s manufacturing sector performance in the first quarter of 2019 was poor, following the myriads of operating challenges hindering the sustenance and the growth of the sector. This was despite the numerous policies designed to buoy the real sector of the economy. MAN in its aggregate Manufacturers CEOs Confidence Index (MCCI) for the first quarter of 2019 made available to New Telegraph yesterday in Lagos, showed that manufacturing index stood at 51.3 points, which was slightly above the 50 points benchmarks of good performance as general macroeconomic condition foreign exchange, lending rate, credit to the manufacturing sector and capital expenditure of the government.